{"sessionId": "9dd316", "hypothesisId": "H11,H12", "location": "talkshow_channel.py:speaking_turn", "message": "speaking turn prompt", "data": {"speaker": "DJ Spark", "turn_kind": "react", "user_prompt": "Current topic: Iran's Mehrabad Airport set on fire by IDF\n\nRecent transcript:\nCornelius Thatch: Well now, that reminds me of the time I watched a bridge get torched during a dispute over trading rights \u2014 and you know what stuck with me? It wasn't who was right or wrong. It was that once you burn the infrastructure, you burn the ordinary people's ability to move, to live, to escape. This airport business \u2014 I think we're asking the wrong question if we're just keeping score on who hit whom. The real question is: when we destroy a nation's lifelines, what are we saying about how we solve problems", "topic": "Iran's Mehrabad Airport set on fire by IDF", "transcript_len": 1}, "timestamp": 1772970274126}
